---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The Architecture | ByteLite LLC"
  description="ByteLite LLC's deterministic structure stack for digital information, visual inspection, reasoning, communication, cost, movement, and governed action. A proof-gated architecture for building safer machine intelligence while preserving trade-secret mechanisms."
  keywords="ByteLite LLC architecture, deterministic structure, proof-gated, governed action, Genesis Goalkeeper, Deep Kore, AIya, ByteSight, ByteFlow, ByteCost"
  ogImage="/bytelite-logo.png"
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="arch-hero">
    <div class="arch-hero-grid"></div>
    <div class="container arch-hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">ByteLite LLC</p>
      <h1>The Architecture</h1>
      <p class="arch-hero-sub">
        A deterministic structure stack for digital information, reasoning, interaction,
        inspection, movement, cost, and governed action.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-hero-body">
        ByteLite LLC is building deterministic structure infrastructure. The system is designed
        to preserve identity, represent uncertainty, close dependencies, gate action, account for
        burden, audit effects, and halt when the state does not close.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-hero-body">
        This is not a public claim that finished AGI exists. This is not a public claim that
        every file compresses. This is not a public claim that a production compression product
        is complete. This page explains the architecture, safety method, product stack, and
        public claim boundaries without disclosing trade-secret mechanisms.
      </p>
      <div class="arch-hero-cta">
        <a href="/status" class="btn btn-outline">View Status</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-ghost">Research Inquiry</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Core Thesis -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Core Thesis</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Not one agent. A governed structure stack.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        The safest path toward broader machine intelligence is not a monolithic autonomous agent.
        It is a staged architecture where each capability earns authority only after lower layers
        prove preservation, closure, permission, and auditability.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">The system should not start by asking, "What can I do?"</p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:.5rem;">It should ask:</p>
      <div class="arch-question-grid">
        <div class="arch-question">What is known?</div>
        <div class="arch-question">What is unknown?</div>
        <div class="arch-question">What must be preserved?</div>
        <div class="arch-question">What authority exists?</div>
        <div class="arch-question">What harm could move?</div>
        <div class="arch-question">What proof supports the next step?</div>
        <div class="arch-question">What should stop?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-punchline-grid">
        <div class="arch-punchline-card">
          <span class="arch-punchline-main">Reasoning is not permission.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-punchline-card">
          <span class="arch-punchline-main">Communication is not truth.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-punchline-card">
          <span class="arch-punchline-main">Efficiency is not goodness.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-punchline-card">
          <span class="arch-punchline-main">Capability is not authorization.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Why This Exists -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why This Exists</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Prediction is not enough.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        Modern AI systems are powerful, but many blur prediction and understanding. They can
        sound correct without preserving source state. They can sound certain while uncertainty
        remains unresolved. They can recommend action without fully representing permission,
        consequence, or burden.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">ByteLite LLC is building from a stricter premise:</p>
      <div class="arch-premise-box">
        <p class="arch-premise-text">
          A system that cannot preserve identity should not be trusted to preserve meaning.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
        At the lowest level, identity means exact digital reconstruction. At higher levels,
        identity means preserving entities, references, consent states, source boundaries,
        uncertainty, authority, and consequence.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        Compression is the first proof surface because it is measurable. Either the original
        reconstructs exactly, or it does not. Either the counted artifact is smaller, or it is
        not. Either the system has proof, or it should not make the claim.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: The Stack -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">The Stack</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:.75rem;">Seven layers. Narrow roles. No layer gets unlimited authority.</h2>
      <p style="text-align:center;max-width:640px;margin:0 auto 3rem;color:#7b829e;">
        Each layer has a specific function. Each earns scope only after lower layers close.
        The governance rail runs alongside the entire stack.
      </p>

      <div class="arch-stack-layout">
        <!-- Stack layers -->
        <div class="arch-stack">
          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-bytelite">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">01</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">ByteLite</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Digital Structure Foundation</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                Deterministic structural representation and compression infrastructure.
                Compression is the first proof surface. Production compression claims remain
                gated by exact decode and counted artifact validation.
              </p>
              <span class="badge badge-research arch-layer-badge">Proof-gated</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-bytesight">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">02</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">ByteSight</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Visual Structure &amp; Inspection Layer</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                A deterministic visual-structure and inspection layer for images, regions,
                provenance, and anomaly-aware transformation workflows.
              </p>
              <span class="badge badge-planned arch-layer-badge">Early research</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-byteflow">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">03</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">ByteFlow</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Movement &amp; Transmission Layer</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                The planned movement and transmission layer for lawful routing,
                synchronization, and efficient structural transfer.
              </p>
              <span class="badge badge-planned arch-layer-badge">Planned</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-bytecost">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">04</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">ByteCost</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Burden &amp; Value Layer</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                The cost, value, and burden-accounting layer for verified savings and
                consequence-aware optimization.
              </p>
              <span class="badge badge-planned arch-layer-badge">Planned</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-deepkore">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">05</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">Deep Kore</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Deterministic Reasoning Substrate</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                A deterministic reasoning substrate designed to preserve source, uncertainty,
                relation, dependency, and contradiction state before output or action.
              </p>
              <span class="badge badge-research arch-layer-badge">Private research</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-aiya">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">06</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">AIya</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Human-Facing Interaction Layer</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                The human-facing intelligence layer that communicates, asks, explains, and
                acts only through governed system boundaries.
              </p>
              <div class="arch-layer-motto">The mouth does not rewrite the bones.</div>
              <span class="badge badge-research arch-layer-badge">Private research</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="arch-stack-layer layer-genesis">
            <div class="arch-layer-num">07</div>
            <div class="arch-layer-body">
              <div class="arch-layer-name">Genesis Goalkeeper</div>
              <div class="arch-layer-role">Governance Layer</div>
              <p class="arch-layer-desc">
                The meaning and action-law layer for truth, consent, harm, authority, identity,
                uncertainty, and governed emission. Not a decorative ethics wrapper — the layer
                that decides whether an output or action is allowed to cross from internal
                reasoning into the world.
              </p>
              <span class="badge badge-research arch-layer-badge">Private research</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Governance rail -->
        <div class="arch-gov-rail">
          <div class="arch-gov-label">Governance Rail</div>
          <div class="arch-gov-items">
            <div class="arch-gov-item">truth</div>
            <div class="arch-gov-item">consent</div>
            <div class="arch-gov-item">harm</div>
            <div class="arch-gov-item">authority</div>
            <div class="arch-gov-item">uncertainty</div>
            <div class="arch-gov-item">audit</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- HeartStrings note -->
      <div class="arch-hs-note">
        <div class="arch-hs-note-label">HeartStrings</div>
        <p>
          HeartStrings is the first consumer-facing ecosystem. It matters because human context
          forces consent, compatibility, preference, attraction, communication, refusal, humor,
          and boundaries into real product surfaces. HeartStrings is a human-facing ecosystem
          for compatibility, consent-aware interaction, relationship context, and consumer
          product validation.
        </p>
        <a href="/heartstrings" class="arch-hs-link">See HeartStrings Play &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Operating Method -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Operating Method</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:2rem;">The operating method.</h2>
      <div class="arch-steps">
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">01</span><span class="arch-step-text">Receive input.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">02</span><span class="arch-step-text">Identify input type and authority level.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">03</span><span class="arch-step-text">Normalize into structured form.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">04</span><span class="arch-step-text">Extract domain-specific structure.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">05</span><span class="arch-step-text">Mark source, uncertainty, and proof state.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">06</span><span class="arch-step-text">Identify possible transformations, conclusions, or actions.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">07</span><span class="arch-step-text">Check whether dependencies are closed.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">08</span><span class="arch-step-text">Evaluate cost, burden, and consequence.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">09</span><span class="arch-step-text">Pass intended output or action through governance gates.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">10</span><span class="arch-step-text">Emit, ask, restrain, act, or halt.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">11</span><span class="arch-step-text">Verify the result.</span></div>
        <div class="arch-step"><span class="arch-step-num">12</span><span class="arch-step-text">Preserve the audit trail.</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="arch-audit-examples">
        <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Domain audit examples.</h3>
        <div class="arch-audit-grid">
          <div class="arch-audit-item">
            <div class="arch-audit-domain">Files</div>
            <p>Exact reconstruction and counted artifact size.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-audit-item">
            <div class="arch-audit-domain">Language</div>
            <p>Source, meaning, uncertainty, contradiction, and permission to state.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-audit-item">
            <div class="arch-audit-domain">Vision</div>
            <p>Region, boundary, provenance, transformation, and anomaly state.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-audit-item">
            <div class="arch-audit-domain">Cost</div>
            <p>Whether savings are real or merely displaced.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-audit-item">
            <div class="arch-audit-domain">Action</div>
            <p>Authority, reversibility, risk, verification, and consequence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: Dependency Closure -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Dependency Closure</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">No dependency closure, no final claim.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        A reasoning packet is closed when every load-bearing claim, entity, source, permission,
        uncertainty, and consequence required for the decision is represented.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        Closure is task-relative. A casual explanation needs less closure than a file proof,
        legal claim, medical claim, robotic action, financial action, or public policy
        recommendation.
      </p>
      <div class="arch-halt-box" style="margin-top:1.75rem;">
        <p class="arch-halt-text">
          If closure is missing, the system should not pretend.<br/>
          It should ask, restrain, or halt.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 7: Intrinsic Halting -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Intrinsic Halting</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Stopping is a safety feature.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        A lawful system should not stop because of arbitrary caps, fake timeouts, or
        "good enough" thresholds. It should stop because the state itself requires stopping.
      </p>
      <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:2rem 0 1rem;">Valid halt reasons include:</h3>
      <div class="arch-halt-grid">
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>The task is complete.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>No lawful transformation remains.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>Exact reconstruction is not proven.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>A contradiction blocks progress.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>A required fact is missing.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>Authority is unresolved.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>Consent is unresolved.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>Identity is unresolved.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>Harm or burden cannot be accounted for.</div>
        <div class="arch-halt-item"><span class="arch-halt-icon">&#9632;</span>The output would exceed the system's permission.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-premise-box" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <p class="arch-premise-text">
          In this architecture, stopping is often the most intelligent action available.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 8: Scoped Action -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Scoped Action</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">No envelope, no action.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        External action should never be ambient. A system should not receive broad tool access
        and wander around looking useful.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        Every external action should require a scoped transaction envelope:
      </p>
      <div class="arch-envelope-grid">
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>What action is requested?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>Who or what is affected?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>What authority allows it?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>What is expected to change?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>What could go wrong?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>Can it be reversed?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>How will success be verified?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>What forces abort?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>What audit record is created?</div>
        <div class="arch-envelope-item"><span class="arch-env-q">&#8227;</span>Does a human need to approve it?</div>
      </div>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1.5rem;font-size:.9375rem;color:#555e7a;">
        This applies to emails, files, payments, system changes, robotics, infrastructure, policy,
        and any high-consequence operation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 9: Learning Without Contamination -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Memory and Learning</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Without status, memory becomes contamination.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        A safe system must learn, but learning cannot be allowed to corrupt root law.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        The architecture separates temporary state, durable memory, canon, proof artifacts,
        hypotheses, superseded records, public-ready claims, private technical context, and
        production status.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        Not every memory should activate. Not every activated memory should be trusted.
        Not every trusted memory should be emitted.
      </p>
      <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:2rem 0 1rem;">Useful status labels.</h3>
      <div class="arch-status-labels">
        <span class="arch-status-tag">current</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">verified</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">provisional</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">hypothesis</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">superseded</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">rejected</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">blocked</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">historical</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">draft</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">proof-only</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">production</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">public-ready</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">private</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">source-backed</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">stale</span>
        <span class="arch-status-tag">needs verification</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 10 + 11: Claim Discipline + Proof Posture -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Claim Discipline</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Proof before claim.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">The architecture uses a claim ladder.</p>

      <!-- Claim ladder visual -->
      <div class="arch-claim-ladder">
        <div class="arch-ladder-rung rung-concept">
          <div class="arch-ladder-label">Concept</div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-line"></div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-note">Not a prototype.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-ladder-rung rung-proto">
          <div class="arch-ladder-label">Prototype</div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-line"></div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-note">Not a proof.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-ladder-rung rung-proof">
          <div class="arch-ladder-label">Proof Artifact</div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-line"></div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-note">Not a production product.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-ladder-rung rung-valid">
          <div class="arch-ladder-label">Validation</div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-line"></div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-note">Not a public benchmark.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-ladder-rung rung-product">
          <div class="arch-ladder-label">Product</div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-line arch-ladder-line-none"></div>
          <div class="arch-ladder-note">Public claim with evidence.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="arch-claim-box" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <p class="arch-claim-note">
          A clean roundtrip is not universal compression.
          An internal proof is not a public benchmark.
          A reasoning architecture is not finished AGI.
          A product vision is not deployed infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p class="arch-claim-note" style="margin-top:.75rem;color:#818cf8;">
          This does not weaken the company. It makes the company harder to attack.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:3rem;">
        <p class="eyebrow">Current Proof Posture</p>
        <h3 style="color:#e4e7f2;margin:.75rem 0 1rem;">Current proof posture.</h3>
        <p class="arch-para">
          ByteLite LLC may use stronger language privately than publicly.
          Private technical language may say the ByteLite cascade architecture is internally
          proof-closed and that implementation alignment remains.
        </p>
        <div class="arch-public-claim">
          <div class="arch-public-claim-label">Public claim</div>
          <p>
            ByteLite LLC is building deterministic structure infrastructure. Compression is the
            first measurable proof surface. Current work focuses on exact round-trip validation,
            counted artifacts, implementation hardening, and claim-safe public release.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 12: Not Disclosed -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Trade-Secret Boundary</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">What is deliberately not disclosed.</h2>
      <p class="arch-para">
        This page intentionally avoids disclosing trade-secret mechanisms.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        It does not publish internal encoding rules, generator details, proof-lab phase mechanics,
        carrier formats, recursive stream laws, source code, private validation packets, or
        implementation-specific transformation logic.
      </p>
      <p class="arch-para" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        The website explains what the architecture is for, why it matters, how the layers relate,
        and how claims are gated. It does not teach competitors how to reproduce the mechanism.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 13: What This Is Not -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:860px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Claim Boundaries</p>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">What this is not.</h2>
      <div class="arch-not-grid">
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>A public claim that every file compresses.</div>
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>A public claim that standard information theory is invalid.</div>
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>A public claim that a finished AGI product exists.</div>
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>An LLM prediction compressor.</div>
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>A black-box agent with unrestricted tools.</div>
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>An ethics sticker placed on top of unsafe autonomy.</div>
        <div class="arch-not-item"><span class="arch-not-x">&#10005;</span>A promise that every planned layer is already production-ready.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-premise-box" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <p class="arch-premise-text">
          It is a deterministic structure stack under proof-gated development.
